article_title: Wall Street Journal Wins Investigative Pulitzer
article_text:
The Wall Street Journal won a Pulitzer Prize, journalism’s highest honor, for a series of articles exposing abuses in the Medicare system.

The New York Times won three Pulitzer Prizes, the most of any news organization, including awards for investigative reporting, international reporting and feature photography. Bloomberg News won its first Pulitzer ever, for explanatory reporting, while the Los Angeles Times won in the feature...
